Transit authorities earn revenue splits from advertising sales, possibly alleviating the need for increased fare prices or community tax rates.  Commuter Advertising's media portfolio includes: >> Location- and time-based digital onboard media >> Onboard video and digital signage >> In-station digital media >> SMS campaigns >> Transit signage >> Transit station naming rights >> Website advertising Visit commuter-advertising.com/media for an in-depth look at CA's portfolio. Founded in 2007, CommuterAds is headquartered in Dayton, Ohio and currently operates in partnership with eleven transit authorities throughout the US, in cities including: Atlanta, GA, Jacksonville and Tampa, FL; Champaign and Chicago, IL; Lexington, KY; Kansas City, MO, San Bernardino CA; and Cincinnati, Cleveland, Dayton and Toledo, OH. CommuterAds reaches more than 250 million rides annually, creates over 2B impressions and is always expanding into new markets.
